		{"id":"750eb7b86ca7ee3f","type":"text","text":"[自 1974 年以来，S&P 500 指数在每次泡沫高点之前的三年内都上涨了 100% 或更多，这是 DataTrek 分析团队的研究结果。然而，当前的 S&P 500 指数并未达到这一水平，因此历史数据表明，目前的投资者信心尚未达到不健康的最大值，我们可以安全地将“泡沫风险”从股市关切列表中剔除](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)[1](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)。\n\n[以下是自 1974 年以来 S&P 500 指数每日 3 年滚动价格回报的图表，其中显示了四个三年期收益超过 100% 的情况：1987 年、1999 年、2012 年和 2021 年。值得注意的是，2012 年的情况是在大金融危机之后，股市继续上涨了数年，而其他极强的三年期涨幅均以更糟糕的结果收场。因此，尽管目前的情况并不保证进一步的收益，但我们无需担心投资者信心已达到顶峰。我们继续看好美国大盘股](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)[1](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)。\n\n[虽然 DataTrek 的观点并非共识，但值得注意的是，Apollo 首席经济学家 Torsten Sløk 在上周日的一篇文章中指出，S&P 500 指数中排名前十的公司目前的估值比上世纪 90 年代中期科技泡沫时期的前十名公司更高。他在文章中发布了下图，说明当前的人工智能泡沫比 90 年代更大](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)[1](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)：\n\n!Apollo’s chart\n\n[请注意，这只是一种有趣的比较，而不是科学准确的测量方式。](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)[1](https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/stock-market-outlook-sp500-bubble-crash-investors-financial-fed-tech-2024-2)","x":1120,"y":-660,"width":660,"height":413},
		{"id":"2d4e38bcaee62459","type":"text","text":"During the three years leading up to bubble peaks, U.S. stocks have risen 100% or more. The S&P 500 is nowhere near that this time around. The S&P 500's torrid and top-heavy advance over the past year has convinced some bearish investors that U.S. stocks are in a bubble. But history says otherwise. Since 1974, the S&P 500 has risen 100% of more during the three years that preceded every bubble peak, according to an analysis from a team of analysts at DataTrek. ","x":460,"y":-560,"width":457,"height":366},
